claim.claim-text:
1. A reciprocating saw, comprising:
a housing;
a reciprocating shaft supported within the housing, the reciprocating shaft having a longitudinal axis, a first end, and a second end opposite the first end;
locking assembly supported by the housing at the first end of the reciprocating shaft and selectively moveable between a first position and a second position;
a cutting blade provided at the first end of the reciprocating shaft; and
a drive mechanism provided at the second end of the reciprocating shaft and configured to drive the reciprocating shaft in a substantially reciprocating motion relative to the housing while at the same time allowing the reciprocating shaft to substantially rotate about the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft independent of the housing;
wherein the drive mechanism comprises a drive bushing configured to provide reciprocating motion to the reciprocating shaft when driven by a drive fork;
wherein when the locking assembly is in the first position the reciprocating shaft is configured to substantially reciprocate relative to the housing but remain substantially rotationally fixed relative to the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft, and wherein when the locking assembly is in the second position the reciprocating shaft is configured to substantially reciprocate relative to the housing while at the same time substantially rotating about the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft independent of the housing.

4. A method for allowing a scrolling cutting feature for a reciprocating saw, comprising:
providing a housing extending between a first end and a working end of the saw;
providing a reciprocating shaft supported within the housing, the reciprocating shaft having a longitudinal axis, a first end of the reciprocating shaft provided at the working end of the saw, and a second end opposite of the first end;
providing a blade at the first end of the reciprocating shaft;
providing a driving mechanism at the second end of the reciprocating shaft, the driving mechanism configured to drive the reciprocating shaft in a substantially reciprocating motion about the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft relative the housing; and
providing a locking mechanism supported by the housing at the first end of the reciprocating shaft and selectively moveable between a first position and a second position;
providing a locking bushing selectively engaged with the locking mechanism and configured to be slidably coupled to the reciprocating shaft such that the locking bushing rotates with the reciprocating shaft when the locking mechanism is in the second position, the locking bushing having an inner surface defining at least one locking position;
wherein when the locking mechanism is in the first position the reciprocating shaft is configured to substantially reciprocate relative to the housing but remain substantially rotationally fixed relative to the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft;
wherein when the locking mechanism is in the second position the reciprocating shaft is configured to substantially reciprocate relative to the housing and at the same time substantially rotate about the longitudinal axis of the reciprocating shaft independent of the housing.
